Unfortunately, the it led to the rather unsavoury scenes in the French city, which has a huge Algerian population.

The result meant that, after four attempts, they finally made it out of the World Cup group stage, which is an even more impressive feat considering they failed to even score in South Africa four years ago - only managing to get a point off a woeful England side (also managed by Capello).

Algeria will now play Germany in the last-16, where they will look to gain revenge for the infamous controversy surrounding their exit in 1982 - when West Germany and Austria played out a 1-0 victory to ensure that both teams would qualify.

